<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAROLD MCCUSKER; PROTESTANT PARTY LEADER IN NORTHERN IRELAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harold McCusker, 50, a schoolteacher who became prominent in Northern Ireland 
politics. 
</P>
<P>
He was a member of the British Parliament for 16 years, representing the 
Official Unionists, the mainstream Protestant party in Northern Ireland. He was 
party deputy leader from 1982. McCusker was an eloquent speaker and campaigner 
for tougher measures against the Irish Republican Army, which is fighting to 
rid Northern Ireland of British rule. Like most Northern Ireland Protestants, 
McCusker opposed the 1985 Anglo-Irish Agreement that gave the Irish Republic a 
say in running the province. But he later became critical of older colleagues 
for failing to come up with an alternative to the pact. In Belfast on Monday of 
cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
