<HEADLINE>
<P>
SECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Please allow me to publicly correct a part of my letter ("Secord Gets 
Probation," Feb. 2) and to publicly apologize to Gen. Richard V. Secord for not 
standing and fighting this injustice like a man. 
</P>
<P>
The fact is that he is doing just that. 
</P>
<P>
Gen. Secord writes, "I filed an appeal against the sentence" the day following 
his sentence, Jan. 25. "I still maintain that what we did during Iran/Contra 
was right, proper and legal." 
</P>
<P>
Gen. Secord concludes, "President Reagan has, in my opinion, behaved 
disgracefully. . . . No commander in chief should desert his men -- ever!" 
</P>
<P>
EDWIN O. LEARNARD 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
