<HEADLINE>
<P>
PUBLIC BATHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Throughout history, man has enjoyed public bathing. He has delighted in laying 
back at a pool, stream, river, hot spring, or ocean, getting clean. 
</P>
<P>
The Roman public baths must have been wonderful. America could use the idea 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Plenty of hot water and heat are available at our power plants. Because of the 
nature of the electricity-producing cycle, 65% of the fuel used to produce 
electricity is wasted as heat. That's a lot of waste heat. Clouds of steam can 
be seen rising above our power plants on cold mornings. 
</P>
<P>
So, at a steam plant, we make a nice little park with free showers and washing 
facilities for clothes. Cost would be negligible. 
</P>
<P>
Travelers would use the spas. People living in motor homes would. Kids would. 
The homeless would. 
</P>
<P>
Public baths are very civilized things. They are right in line with the 
President's idea of a gentler, kinder America. 
</P>
<P>
ROGER DURHAM 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
