</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bye Bye 45s?The Tower Records chain issued an in-house memo telling its store 
managers and buyers to "not purchase any seven-inch vinyl new release or hit 
singles from any vendor." 
</P>
<P>
Tower was one of the last champions of the vinyl 45, and has prided itself on 
continuing to make vinyl records available to its customers despite drooping 
sales. The chain was one of the last that stocked a wide selection of the 
singles. Tower will continue to purchase oldies singles, however. BETH KLEID 
</P>
