<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: ZENITH NATIONAL PROFIT FALLS 43% IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zenith National Insurance Corp. said its fourth-quarter profit tumbled 43% from 
a year earlier on little change in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
The Woodland Hills insurer said its net income dropped to $5.3 million in the 
quarter that ended Dec. 31 from $9.24 million a year earlier, while its revenue 
inched up to $115.9 million from $115.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
The latest quarter reflected, among other things, a net loss of about $2 
million related to the earthquake in Northern California last fall, Zenith 
said. 
</P>
<P>
For all of 1989, Zenith's profit fell 11%, to $41.1 million from $46.3 million 
the previous year, and its annual revenue rose to $483.9 million from $472 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
