<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: PINKERTON'S PLANNING PUBLIC STOCK OFFERING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pinkerton's Inc., the nation's biggest security guard company, plans to raise 
up to $21 million with an initial public offering of 1.3 million common shares. 
</P>
<P>
In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the Van Nuys-based 
company said the stock is expected to sell for $14 to $16 a share. The company 
also registered 666,667 shares that might be sold by Pinkerton's President 
Thomas W. Wathen. 
</P>
<P>
Wathen, through his solely owned California Plant Protection Inc., bought 
Pinkerton's from American Brands Inc. for $100 million two years ago, and named 
the combined company Pinkerton's. In its SEC filing, Pinkerton's said proceeds 
from the stock sale would be used for repaying the cost of the acquisition. 
</P>
