<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDELMAN OBTAINS PAPERS FOR 5TH TERM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County Supervisor Ed Edelman, who represents the Westside and parts 
of the Eastside and San Fernando Valley, took out nominating papers Monday to 
seek a fifth term. 
</P>
<P>
The Democrat picked up the documents on the first day of the filing period at 
the office of the county registrar-recorder in Commerce. He has until March 9 
to return them along with the $898 filing fee and at least 20 nominating 
signatures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
