<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST JAVA VOLCANO KILLS 17 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JAKARTA, Indonesia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A low-level eruption of Mt. Kelud, a 5,679-foot volcano in East Java, continued 
for a third day Monday. It has killed at least 17 people. 
</P>
