<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: A'S CANSECO SETTLES FOR $2-MILLION DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jose Canseco agreed Monday to a one-year, $2-million contract with the Oakland 
Athletics, a $400,000 raise over last season but well shy of the huge totals 
other superstars have received this winter. 
</P>
<P>
The right fielder was scheduled to have an arbitration hearing on Wednesday. He 
wanted $2.2 million and the A's offered $1.6 million, same as last season. 
</P>
<P>
Second baseman Mike Gallego also avoided arbitration by agreeing to a two-year, 
$1,065,000 contract. He'll get $475,000 this year, $540,000 in 1991 and a 
$50,000 signing bonus. Mark McGwire, whose hearing is set for Friday, is the 
only player left on the A's arbitration list. 
</P>
</TEXT>
