<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ANTARCTICA; 
</P>
<P>
ITALIAN, GERMAN JOIN IN UNAIDED CROSSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Italian Reinhold Messner and West German Arved Fuchs became the first to cross 
Antarctica without the aid of dogs or machinery. A West German magazine said 
they finished their 1,550-mile trek after 91 days, using sails and wind power 
to help pull their sledges. 
</P>
