<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK; 
</P>
<P>
HUNDREDS ESCORT BODY OF SLAIN RABBI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hundreds of weeping ultra-orthodox Jews marched through Brooklyn accompanying 
the body of a popular rabbi killed by a robber. Rabbi Cheskel Werzberger, 58, a 
World War II concentration camp survivor and a leader of Brooklyn's largest 
Satmar synagogue, died at Bellevue Hospital. He had been shot Thursday by a 
gunman who then stole the rabbi's car to chase a courier believed to be 
carrying precious gems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
