</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arco Says Hola to Spain: Atlantic Richfield Co. has signed a licensing and 
joint venture agreement with Indalsa, a Madrid-based restaurant operator, to 
open more than 600 am/pm mini-markets in Spain and Portugal. 
</P>
<P>
It marks the first move by am/pm International, an Arco subsidiary, into 
Europe. Arco signed similar agreements in 1988 with companies in Japan and 
Taiwan. Arco has more than 700 am/pm convenience stores in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
