<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Jolla-based Intermark has completed the sale of its Munson Sporting Goods 
Co. subsidiary to Dayton, Ohio-based Outdoor Sports Headquarters for an 
undisclosed price. Munson, a leading sporting goods wholesaler in the Western 
U.S., reported $30.1 million in net sales for the nine-month period ended Dec. 
31, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Outdoor Sports Headquarters, the nation's largest full-service distributor of 
hunting, fishing, camping and archery equipment, is a wholly owned subsidiary 
of Dayton-based Centuri Inc. Its annual revenue total rose to about $250 
million with the Munson acquisition. 
</P>
<P>
"Though Munson has become a pacesetter in its market, we have come to believe 
that Munson's best prospects for future growth can be achieved through 
assimilation into the Outdoor Sports organization and its commitment to the 
industry," Intermark President and Chief Executive Charles R. Scott said 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Intermark on Monday reported that it had exercised an 
option to purchase 1 million shares of stock in Triton Group Ltd. The purchase 
gave Intermark voting power over 51.6% of Triton's stock. 
</P>
<P>
Intermark is a billion dollar operating/holding company listed on the American 
Stock Exchange. 
</P>
