<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dana Parsons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FAMILY FEUD: They're sister schools, but it isn't uncommon for one UC campus to 
covet another's staff, as evidenced by Berkeley's interest in Irvine's No. 2 
administrator, Chang-Lin Tien. . . . UCI evolutionary biologist Francisco 
Ayala, for example, was recruited from UC Davis. . . . But fear of too much 
bloodletting led UC system officials to circulate a secret memo a while back 
cautioning campuses against internecine bidding wars that would drive up 
salaries. . . . Tien, possibly the next UC Berkeley chancellor, may learn his 
fate when the regents meet Thursday. Dana Parsons 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
