<P>
MAN SHOT IN BACK DURING WALK IN PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 31-year-old Los Angeles man was shot once in the back while walking Sunday 
night in Center Park. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Martinez was in stable condition Monday at Western Medical Center-Santa 
Ana after undergoing surgery. 
</P>
<P>
Martinez told police he was walking alone through the park, located in the 200 
block of South Center Street, when he heard a single gunshot and felt a sharp 
pain in his back. He called paramedics from a nearby phone booth about 7:20 
p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Martinez did not see or hear anyone he could link to the shot. 
There are no suspects in the case, Santa Ana police spokeswoman Maureen Thomas 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"There's always the possibility that it was a stray bullet," Thomas said. "We 
don't have much on this case." 
</P>
<P>
The park is surrounded mostly by businesses and by a few homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
