<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' PREP SOCCER PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
SOME REWARD: MATER DEI OPENS AGAINST SANTA MONICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Winning the Angelus League boys' soccer title didn't do Mater Dei High School a 
lot of good as far as the Southern Section 4-A playoffs are concerned. 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs (15-6-2), who haven't lost since mid-December, clinched the league 
title with a 2-1 victory over Servite Thursday. Their reward is Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
Although Santa Monica of the Bay League enters the playoffs as the third-seeded 
team, the Vikings were ranked among the division's top 10 teams most of the 
season. Two weeks ago, Santa Monica was ranked 10th in the 4-A poll. 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs play the Vikings (16-9-2) Friday in a first-round game. 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs haven't lost in 12 games, but they haven't dominated opponents on 
the scoreboard either. In an earlier game against Servite, the Monarchs outshot 
the Friars, 19-2, but had to settle for a 1-1 tie. "We had a problem all season 
with finishing off shots," Coach Martin Stringer said. 
</P>
<P>
In other 4-A first-round games Friday: 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View (14-4-5) plays at Hawthorne (19-2-6), the fourth-seeded team, and 
Servite (10-10-4) is at Edison (13-5-5). 
</P>
<P>
Alta Loma (16-8-5) plays at Marina (14-6) in a wild-card game Wednesday. The 
winner plays at Don Lugo (15-4-6). 
</P>
<P>
In 3-A first-round games Thursday: 
</P>
<P>
Foothill (17-4-5) plays at Redlands (18-4-2); Compton (10-5-1) at Santa Ana 
(14-3-6); Paramount (11-3-2) at El Toro (10-3-2); Dana Hills (13-6-2) at Canyon 
(11-7-5); Los Altos (9-5-3) at Mission Viejo (13-6-5). 
</P>
<P>
In 2-A first-round games Friday: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Maria (9-9-2) plays at Cypress (16-4-3), the third-seeded team; Los 
Alamitos (7-8-8) at La Quinta (9-7-5); Valencia (9-6-5) at Montebello (17-1-3); 
Calexico (8-6) at Esperanza (13-4-5); Woodbridge (10-8-2) at Anaheim (9-3-4); 
Pacifica (9-8-1) at Ganesha (17-4-1); Trabuco Hills (9-9-3) at Santiago 
(15-3-4); Bonita (6-10-5) at Brea-Olinda (13-7-2); Kennedy (11-7) at Laguna 
Hills (19-5). 
</P>
<P>
Orange (17-0-3), the only undefeated team in the section, is the top-seeded 
team in the division and has a first-round bye. 
</P>
<P>
In 1-A first-round games Thursday: 
</P>
<P>
Temple City (10-12-1) plays at Sunny Hills, the fourth-seeded team; Bosco Tech 
(15-5-1) at Newport Harbor (16-3-6); St. Anthony (9-8-2) at Saddleback 
(14-4-2); San Dimas at Sonora (7-10-3). 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton (6-12-3) plays at Estancia (9-2-3) today in a wild-card game. The 
winner plays at El Segundo (16-2-2) Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
In small school first-round games Friday: 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian (13-6-1) plays at Miraleste (16-3-0); Santa Margarita (10-7) 
at Temecula Valley (17-7-1). 
</P>
<P>
Orange Lutheran (14-6-2) is the third-seeded team in the division and has a 
first-round bye. 
</P>
<P>
* COMPLETE PAIRINGS: C11 
</P>
