<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTENDORF LEADS ST.MARGARET'S INTO SMALL SCHOOLS PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. Margaret's High School is the second-seeded team in the Southern Section 
Small Schools Division boys' basketball playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
The Tartans (17-4) have 14 consecutive basketball victories dating back to 
mid-December. 
</P>
<P>
They are led by center Ryan Westendorf, who is averaging 25 points and 19 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
All four of the Tartans' losses came against 1-A schools and three were in the 
La Jolla tournament. 
</P>
<P>
"We had just gotten several of our players out from football," Coach Rick Bauer 
said. "We had only had two practices with the entire team." 
</P>
<P>
Westendorf has been one of the most dominant players on the Small Schools level 
this season. However, the Tartans don't rely completely on him. Guard Dan 
Campaigne is averaging 17.3 points per game. 
</P>
<P>
Three other Orange County teams -- Claremont, California Lutheran and St. 
Michael's -- will compete in the Small Schools division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
