<P>
Three suspected members of a Communist death squad shot and killed the mayor of 
a town just outside Manila today, the military reported. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Felino Maquinay of Carmona died on the spot with three bullet wounds in 
the head, said Capt. Romeo Gullas, provincial operations chief of the 
Philippine Constabulary. 
</P>
