Three unidentified youths, believed to be members of the Communist New People's 
Army, approached Maquinay as he was having lunch and opened fire at close range 
with pistols, Gullas said. 
</P>
<P>
Maquinay's bodyguard and his driver, too surprised by the attack to protect 
him, were unharmed, Gullas added. The gunmen fled in a commandeered car. 
