<HEADLINE>
<P>
'BLIND FAITH' KEEPS NBC ON TOP 85TH WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NBC had faith -- the first half of the miniseries "Blind Faith" on Sunday night 
-- to help it stay on top for the 85th week out of the last 86, it was reported 
today. 
</P>
<P>
An interesting thing happened to the networks on the way to the ratings war on 
Sunday -- during the two-hour movie window, they had a combined audience share 
of 78%, considerably higher than the 69% they usually average. 
</P>
<P>
Two of the three competing shows -- "Blind Faith" on NBC (ranking 8th in the 
listings) and the terrifying "Miracle Landing" on CBS (24th) -- were based on 
real happenings. The theatrical film "Robocop" (23rd) was the ABC entry. 
</P>
<P>
Two other docudramas were less widely watched. The second installment of CBS' 
miniseries, "Family Of Spies," tied for 36th on Tuesday, which is pretty good 
for CBS on a Tuesday. NBC's "Murder in Mississippi" came in 50th, which is not 
good for an NBC Monday movie. 
</P>
<P>
There were two new series bowing in last week -- "Elvis" on ABC and "The 
Bradys" on CBS. 
</P>
<P>
"Elvis," in its special premiere slot following "Roseanne," tied for 20th -- a 
considerable drop from its third-place lead-in. When "Elvis" moved into its 
regular Sunday slot, it dropped to 47th, down precipitously from its lead-in, 
"America's Funniest Home Videos," which again made the top 10. 
</P>
<P>
NBC won the ratings race for the week ending Feb. 11 with a 14.7 rating and a 
24 share, according to the A. C. Nielsen Co. ABC took second place with a 13.2 
rating and a 21 share, while CBS was third with a 12.5 rating and a 20 share. 
</P>
<P>
The 21-week-old season-to-date ratings show NBC with a 14.8 rating and a 25 
share, ABC with a 13.0 rating and a 22 share, and CBS with a 12.3 rating and a 
20 share. 
</P>
<P>
TV RATINGS 
</P>
<P>
Here are the ratings for national prime-time television last week (Feb. 5-11), 
as compiled by the A. C. Nielsen Co. 
</P>
<P>
Program (Network) Rating 
</P>
<P>
1. The Cosby Show (NBC) 22.9 
</P>
<P>
2. Cheers (NBC) 22.8 
</P>
<P>
3. Roseanne (ABC) 22.5 
</P>
<P>
4. A Different World (NBC) 21.9 
</P>
